    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter May 1st with a lineup headlined by **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who earns today\u2019s top mark of 73.24. Despite hitting 8th, his aggressive dynamic platoon advantage against Gallen provides a high-ceiling profile for stolen bases, a category we are prioritizing heavily today given our pursuit of efficiency. **Kazuma Okamoto** (63.91) and **Carson Benge** (62.65) follow closely as our most reliable bats, both benefiting significantly from weak opposing starters\u2014Woods Richardson and Urena, respectively\u2014whose xERAs north of 4.80 create prime environments for run production. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on **Yordan Alvarez** (51.14); while his elite raw talent is undeniable, he faces a daunting matchup against Bennett (1.80 xERA), suppressing his daily efficiency score despite the favorable park factors.\n\nStrategic decisions for today centered on balancing daily caps against defensive mobility. **Junior Caminero** (60.63) remains a start despite facing a tough southpaw in Ray, as his role at the #2 spot provides enough volume to overcome the platoon disadvantage. On the fringe, **Caleb Durbin** (49.84) narrowly edged out our other utility options; while his spot in the 9-hole hurts his run-scoring potential, his elite sprint speed keeps him in the lineup over bench depth like **Josh Smith** or **Luke Raley** to ensure we maintain our competitive advantage in SB. We continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich**, who remains on the IL, and we are holding **Trea Turner**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Colt Keith** in reserve today as they are not currently featured in their respective MLB starting lineups, leaving us with minimal flexibility should late-inning defensive replacements or weather delays occur.",
